{
  "texts": [
    "Alternatively, there's the identity \\(\\cos (180^\\circ + \\theta) = -\\cos \\theta\\), but that's not directly applicable here.",
    "Let me double-check the symmetry properties.",
    "Cosine is an even function, meaning \\(\\cos (-\\theta) = \\cos \\theta\\), which shows symmetry about the y-axis.",
    "The identity \\(\\cos (360^\\circ -\\theta) = \\cos \\theta\\) shows symmetry every full cycle.",
    "But the statement \\(\\cos \\theta = \\cos (180^\\circ -\\theta)\\) isn't generally true."
  ]
}